data.description: Welcome home to this impeccably restored Victorian home, nestled in the historic town of Sudlersville, MD. Built in 1910, this grand residence spans an impressive 4,700 square feet, offering a timeless blend of historic elegance and contemporary comfort. Step into a world of refined living with seven spacious bedrooms, each exuding its own unique character, complemented by additional bonus room space for versatility in utilization. The seamless marriage of old-world craftsmanship and modern convenience is evident throughout the home, showcasing extensive upgrades that include a brand-new roof, furnace, and a chef's dream kitchen. As you enter, you're greeted by newly painted walls that accentuate the intricate details of the Victorian era. The hardwood floors have been masterfully refinished, adding warmth and sophistication to every room. The main floor boasts a distinctive feature—a one-bedroom apartment with its own exterior entrance, providing a perfect guest suite or an opportunity for rental income. The main floor also includes a large family room off of the kitchen with an electric fireplace, formal dining room, and a separate sitting room with a woodstove.  Situated on an expansive acre lot, this property offers more than just a home; it provides a lifestyle. Multiple storage sheds cater to your organizational needs, ensuring ample space for all your belongings. The meticulously landscaped yard is a testament to pride of ownership, creating a serene oasis where you can relax and entertain. This Victorian gem in Sudlersville invites you to be a part of its rich history and make lasting memories within its storied walls. Your dream home awaits—schedule a showing and step into a timeless masterpiece where history and modernity converge seamlessly.
